WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.709
(gate creaks open, shuts)

00:05.834 --> 00:09.000
(footsteps approaching)

00:11.834 --> 00:13.458
COME ON.

00:16.667 --> 00:18.250
COME HERE.

00:27.458 --> 00:31.000
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE PACT?!

00:31.083 --> 00:32.458
DON'T EVER THINK

00:32.542 --> 00:34.667
I'D GO BACK ON A PACT,
ESPECIALLY WITH YOU, BRI.

00:34.792 --> 00:36.083
I DIDN'T MAKE THE PACT.

00:36.166 --> 00:39.500
(clenches teeth)
I BROKE UP WITH HER. JEEZ.

00:40.750 --> 00:44.709
♪♪

00:46.583 --> 00:49.625
OKAY, WHO'S GONNA DRIVE?
BECAUSE YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO

00:49.709 --> 00:52.083
FOLLOW ME DOWN TO FRANKLIN,
OVER TO HIGHLAND,

00:52.208 --> 00:53.667
MAKE A RIGHT INTO THE PARKING STRUCTURE,

00:53.750 --> 00:55.500
PARK ON THE FOURTH FLOOR
NEXT TO THE YELLOW ESCALATOR.

00:55.583 --> 00:56.959
ADAM, REALLY WORKING
ON THOSE CONTROL ISSUES, HUH?

00:57.041 --> 00:59.083
WELL DONE, MY MAN. HEY!

00:59.208 --> 01:02.333
WHO GOT LOST LAST TIME?
IT WAS 10:00. I GOT 3 KIDS.
THAT'S LIKE 3:00 A.M., MAN.

01:02.417 --> 01:04.917
I WAS DISORIENTED. HOW DO YOU PUT UP
WITH THIS GUY.

01:05.041 --> 01:07.000
OH, I TRY NOT TO TALK TO HIM.
HONEY, SODAS.

01:07.083 --> 01:08.417
PUT THESE IN YOUR JACKET.

01:08.542 --> 01:11.041
CUTE, DAVE. I HOPE THE USHER
DOESN'T FRISK YOU.

01:11.166 --> 01:13.875
(woman) YOU TAKE YOUR OWN FOOD
TO THE MOVIES?

01:14.000 --> 01:16.375
WELL, IT'S $12 AN HOUR
FOR THE BABY-SITTER.

01:16.458 --> 01:18.542
IT'S A 5-HOUR MINIMUM. YOU GOT
THE PARKING AND THE MOVIE.

01:18.667 --> 01:20.041
IT'S LIKE 300 BUCKS.

01:20.166 --> 01:21.917
MAYBE YOU SHOULD TRY ROASTING
YOUR OWN TRAIL MIX.

01:22.041 --> 01:23.583
OH, THAT'S FUNNY. WAIT TILL YOU HAVE KIDS.

01:23.709 --> 01:26.458
I'M HAVING ONE, AND I WON'T BE
ROASTING MY OWN TRAIL MIX.

01:26.583 --> 01:28.458
ALL RIGHT, CAN WE PLEASE TAKE ONE CAR?

01:28.583 --> 01:31.959
WE CAN TAKE THE MINIVAN.
WE CAN ALL FIT IN THERE. SOUNDS GOOD.

01:32.083 --> 01:35.083
NO, IT ONLY SEATS SIX. WHAT ABOUT BRIAN?

01:35.208 --> 01:37.291
OH, DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.
I CAN DRIVE MYSELF.

01:37.417 --> 01:40.500
(Adam) WE CAN TAKE BRIAN.
(woman) NO, NO, NO, WE GOTTA
MEET YOUR BOSS AT THAT THING.

01:40.583 --> 01:42.625
(woman) WELL, HE'S MY BROTHER.
HE CAN COME WITH US.

01:42.750 --> 01:44.792
COME WITH US, BRI. (Adam) UH, WE CAN JUST
TAKE HIM DOWN THERE,

01:44.917 --> 01:47.041
AND YOU GUYS CAN BRING HIM BACK HERE.

01:47.125 --> 01:50.542
NO, WE CAN'T TAKE HIM.
MY CAR IS FULL OF<i> COM </i>SHOTS.
<i>COMP </i>SHOTS, HONEY.

01:50.625 --> 01:53.542
YEAH, THAT'S WHAT I SAID.
(woman) YOU KNOW,
LET'S JUST TAKE THREE CARS

01:53.625 --> 01:56.125
LIKE WE DO EVERY OTHER TIME.

01:56.250 --> 01:58.291
GUYS, LOOK, THE SEVENTH WHEEL
HAS HIS LICENSE NOW.

01:58.417 --> 02:01.583
I CAN DRIVE MYSELF.
TECHNICALLY, YOU CAN ONLY BE
A THIRD WHEEL OR A SIXTH WHEEL.

02:01.709 --> 02:03.166
WHAT HAS FIVE WHEELS?

02:03.250 --> 02:05.041
THE 1951 RUBIA WOODIE HAS 5 WHEELS.
OH, REALLY?

02:05.125 --> 02:07.458
AND A 1930 SIDEMOUNTED SEDAN HAS 6.

02:07.542 --> 02:10.959
SO THE SEVENTH WHEEL IS GONNA
MEET YOU GUYS AT THE THEATER.

02:11.083 --> 02:12.959
HE'S TAKING FOUNTAIN, NOT FRANKLIN.

02:13.083 --> 02:14.375
HE'S PARKING BY THE BLUE ESCALATORS,

02:14.458 --> 02:16.667
AND HE'S BUYING HIMSELF A $10 SODA POP.

02:16.792 --> 02:18.458
OOH, BIG SPENDER. NICE.

02:18.583 --> 02:20.959
HEY, DID YOU GET THAT CAR RADIO
FIXED YET, BRI?

02:21.041 --> 02:22.792
(woman) YEAH, RIGHT. GO ROCK OUT, MY MAN.

02:22.917 --> 02:25.291
<i>♪ [QUIRKY ROCK]</i>

02:35.709 --> 02:37.458
THIS IS RIDICULOUS. COME ON.

02:37.583 --> 02:39.959
<i>♪ [CONTINUES]</i>

02:45.125 --> 02:47.583
COME ON, CHANGE.

03:12.917 --> 03:15.250
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

03:15.333 --> 03:16.750
[SCREAMS]

03:16.834 --> 03:19.125
(air bag hissing)

03:21.000 --> 03:22.709
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?!

03:22.834 --> 03:25.792
♪♪

03:25.875 --> 03:27.333
<i>WHAT </i>ARE YOU THINKING?

03:27.458 --> 03:31.250
I MEAN, SERIOUSLY, BRIAN,
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU THINKING?

03:31.375 --> 03:34.375
YOU'RE DATING WHOSE CAR
WHO SMASHED INTO LAST WEEK?

03:34.500 --> 03:37.166
TWO WEEKS AGO. I DIDN'T<i> SMASH </i>INTO HER.

03:37.250 --> 03:39.417
YOU ARE TRISHING. I AM<i> NOT </i>TRISHING.

03:39.542 --> 03:41.959
WHAT'S TRISHING?
TRISH MEADOWS, FIFTH GRADE.

03:42.041 --> 03:44.041
SHE WAS BRIAN'S GIRLFRIEND FOR MONTHS.

03:44.125 --> 03:45.959
CAR GIRL IS<i> NOT </i>TRISHING.

03:46.041 --> 03:47.500
BRIAN WENT STEADY WITH TRISH

03:47.583 --> 03:50.000
EVEN THOUGH HE DIDN'T<i> REALLY</i>
LIKE HER. AAH!

03:50.083 --> 03:53.083
YOU'LL LEARN THIS IS
A SAD CYCLE IN BRIAN'S LIFE.

03:53.208 --> 03:54.500
IS THAT TRUE?

03:54.583 --> 03:56.500
YES, BUT THAT'S NOT WHAT THIS IS.

03:56.583 --> 04:00.000
CAR GIRL IS-- YOU KNOW, SHE'S FINE.

04:00.083 --> 04:01.625
"SHE'S FINE."

04:01.709 --> 04:03.375
OH, THAT SOUNDS LIKE LOVE, BRI.

04:03.500 --> 04:05.166
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED THIS TIME?

04:05.250 --> 04:07.750
I WAS ON MY WAY TO THE MOVIES
TO MEET YOU GUYS.

04:07.875 --> 04:10.250
I HAD AN EXTREMELY MINOR ACCIDENT.

04:10.333 --> 04:11.709
[SCREAMS]

04:11.792 --> 04:13.125
(horns honking)

04:13.250 --> 04:16.250
I'M SO--I'M SO SORRY! I'M SORRY!

04:16.333 --> 04:18.250
<i>THE NEXT THING I KNOW,</i>

04:18.333 --> 04:21.208
<i>THIS GIRL IS STANDING IN FRONT OF ME,</i>

04:21.291 --> 04:23.250
<i>AND I THOUGHT, I DON'T KNOW.</i>

04:23.333 --> 04:25.917
<i>MAYBE I'M SUPPOSED TO MEET THIS GIRL.</i>

04:26.041 --> 04:28.333
<i>ALL OF A SUDDEN, WE'RE BACK AT HER PLACE,</i>

04:28.417 --> 04:32.834
<i>AND WE'RE REALLY, YOU KNOW,</i>
<i>GETTING ALONG GREAT.</i>

04:32.917 --> 04:36.166
<i>I MEAN, SHE'S A BIT OF A CLEAN FREAK.</i>

04:36.250 --> 04:38.417
IT'S DRY-CLEAN ONLY.

04:38.542 --> 04:39.792
WHAT?

04:39.917 --> 04:41.375
SHE'S GOT ISSUES, WHICH IS FINE.

04:41.458 --> 04:44.917
YEAH, IT'S FINE. DUDE, YOU'RE TRISHING.

04:45.041 --> 04:47.917
<i>I'M NOT. SHE HAS SOME WONDERFUL QUALITIES.</i>

04:48.041 --> 04:49.750
(gargling loudly)

04:49.834 --> 04:51.041
(spits)

04:51.125 --> 04:53.709
BABY, WHERE'S YOUR TOOTHBRUSH?

04:53.792 --> 04:56.333
<i>(Adam) YEAH? AND WHAT</i>
ARE<i> HER GOOD QUALITIES?</i>

04:56.458 --> 04:58.667
<i>(Brian) SHE, UH, SHE HAS A DOG.</i>

04:58.792 --> 05:00.542
KISS HIM!

05:00.625 --> 05:03.041
<i>DUDE, I CAN TELL YOU ARE NOT INTO HER.</i>

05:03.125 --> 05:05.125
<i>I AM. LIKE, YESTERDAY WE WENT SHOPPING</i>

05:05.208 --> 05:06.667
<i>FOR A... NEW MATTRESS.</i>

05:06.792 --> 05:08.166
<i>(laughing)</i>

05:08.291 --> 05:10.959
YOU ARE HOPELESS. YOU ARE TRISHING.

05:11.041 --> 05:12.667
YOU'RE NOT HOPELESS. (bottle clinks)

05:12.792 --> 05:15.000
WELL, THAT'S EMPTY.

05:15.125 --> 05:17.000
WELL, WE NEED SOME BEERS.

05:17.125 --> 05:18.959
I'M GONNA BRING YOU BOTH SOME BEERS.

05:19.041 --> 05:21.959
I'M GONNA RUN DOWN THE HILL. OKAY.

05:22.041 --> 05:23.333
ALL RIGHT. LET'S GO.

05:23.458 --> 05:26.625
NO. NO, I WANT YOU TO LISTEN.

05:28.500 --> 05:30.291
NO JOKING AROUND.

05:30.375 --> 05:32.583
OKAY.

05:32.667 --> 05:36.125
I KNOW THAT EVERYBODY THINKS
THAT YOU'RE ONE OF THOSE GUYS.

05:36.208 --> 05:38.834
YOU KNOW, ONE OF THOSE NONCOMMITTAL GUYS.

05:38.959 --> 05:42.709
BUT I KNOW YOU'RE NOT.

05:42.834 --> 05:46.917
WHAT YOU ARE... IS ROMANTIC.

05:47.000 --> 05:51.041
AND YOU'RE A FANTASTIC PERSON.

05:51.166 --> 05:54.166
AND YOU'RE FUNNY.

05:54.250 --> 05:56.166
YOU'RE FUNNY AND YOU'RE...

05:56.291 --> 05:58.166
YOU'RE HOT AND YOU'RE SMART.

05:58.291 --> 06:00.959
YOU'RE A GREAT FRIEND.
YOU'RE EVERYBODY'S FRIEND.

06:01.041 --> 06:02.917
EVERYONE LOVES YOU.

06:03.000 --> 06:04.792
YOU'RE A CATCH, MAN. YOU'RE JUST...

06:04.875 --> 06:06.792
YOU'RE A TOTAL CATCH.

06:06.875 --> 06:10.291
BUT SERIOUSLY, BRIAN, YOU'VE GOT TO STOP.

06:10.375 --> 06:12.291
YOU'VE GOT TO LOOK AT YOURSELF.

06:12.375 --> 06:14.458
LOOK AT YOURSELF IN THE MIRROR, LITERALLY.

06:14.542 --> 06:16.709
(voice echoing softly) ASK YOURSELF,

06:16.792 --> 06:18.542
WHO DO I WANNA BE WITH?

06:18.667 --> 06:21.959
(voice fades)

06:22.041 --> 06:26.291
♪♪

06:36.583 --> 06:40.542
(voice fades up)
...WHO IS WORTH YOUR TIME?

06:40.625 --> 06:43.041
WHO IS SHE?

06:45.792 --> 06:48.375
NO, NO, NO, NO. YOU ARE NOT.

06:48.500 --> 06:51.291
YOU'RE NOT. YOU'RE NOT IN LOVE
WITH MARJORIE.

06:51.375 --> 06:54.291
YOU CAN'T BE, SO YOU'RE NOT.
YOU HEAR ME, HMM?

06:54.375 --> 06:56.208
I'M IN LOVE WITH MARJORIE.

06:56.333 --> 06:58.250
NO, ADAM'S IN LOVE WITH MARJORIE.
YEAH.

06:58.375 --> 07:00.542
ADAM'S YOUR BEST FRIEND. HI.

07:00.625 --> 07:02.667
YEAH, MARJORIE IS, TOO.
MARJORIE'S YOUR FRIEND, TOO.

07:02.750 --> 07:04.333
WELCOME. THIS IS WHAT I'M SAYING.

07:04.417 --> 07:06.083
FOR THE LAST-- ALMOST TWO YEARS--

07:06.166 --> 07:08.667
I'M COMPARING EVERY GIRL
I GO OUT WITH TO HER.

07:08.750 --> 07:10.291
OKAY, THAT DOOR MUST CLOSE.

07:10.417 --> 07:13.166
SHE IS NOT ONLY BEAUTIFUL.
SHE'S BRILLIANT.

07:13.250 --> 07:16.417
SHE'S A PEDIATRICIAN
<i>AND </i>A FOOTBALL FANATIC.

07:16.500 --> 07:19.166
SHE KNOWS MORE ABOUT<i> EVERYTHING </i>THAN I DO.

07:19.250 --> 07:21.166
I'VE BEEN GOING OUT WITH GIRLS,

07:21.250 --> 07:23.583
TRYING TO FIND SOMEONE
HALF AS GREAT AS MARJORIE,

07:23.667 --> 07:26.875
AND SOME OF THESE GIRLS,
DAVE, BY THE WAY, ARE GREAT.

07:26.959 --> 07:28.083
YEAH.

07:28.166 --> 07:30.083
BUT NONE OF THEM ARE HER.

07:30.166 --> 07:32.375
AND NOW I'M DATING CAR GIRL
TO DISTRACT MYSELF

07:32.458 --> 07:34.208
FROM THE INEVITABLE HORRIBLE TRUTH

07:34.291 --> 07:38.083
THAT THE ONE PERSON I'M NOT WITH
IS THE ONE PERSON I LOVE.

07:38.166 --> 07:40.041
OKAY, LISTEN TO ME. THAT DOOR MUST CLOSE.

07:40.125 --> 07:42.208
YOU HEARING ME? YEAH.

07:42.291 --> 07:44.208
TAKE THE KEY, LOCK THE DOOR,

07:44.291 --> 07:46.208
THROW THE KEY AWAY
INTO THE... INDIAN OCEAN.

07:46.291 --> 07:47.667
WHY THE INDIAN OCEAN? I DON'T KNOW.

07:47.792 --> 07:51.625
I JUST PICKED A RANDOM OCEAN.
TAKE THE KEY. TAKE IT.

07:52.959 --> 07:55.291
THERE YOU GO. LOCK THE DOOR.

07:55.417 --> 07:58.083
CLICK. IT'S LOCKED. THROW AWAY THE KEY.

07:59.959 --> 08:01.959
SO PATHETIC. LOOK AT ME.

08:02.041 --> 08:04.125
REPEAT AFTER ME.

08:04.250 --> 08:09.208
MARJORIE IS NOT AN OPTION.

08:12.709 --> 08:16.625
MARJORIE IS NOT AN OPTION.

08:16.750 --> 08:19.834
OH, MAN, I'M GLAD YOU
CAME AROUND. LET'S HAVE A BEER.

08:20.000 --> 08:21.291
I THINK IT'S ELECTRICAL.

08:21.375 --> 08:23.792
THE FUSE BOX IS IN THE TRUNK.

08:23.875 --> 08:26.166
YEAH, WELL, IT KEEPS SPAZZING OUT ON ME

08:26.291 --> 08:28.458
IN THE MIDDLE OF NOWHERE.

08:31.083 --> 08:34.125
HEY, JIMMY.

08:37.333 --> 08:39.417
HEY, UH, TURN THE KEY FOR ME.

08:39.500 --> 08:41.000
YEAH.

08:41.083 --> 08:44.083
HEY, LOVER BUTT,
WHERE'D YOU PUT THE DOG FOOD?

08:44.166 --> 08:45.583
IN THE TOP CUPBOARD.

08:45.667 --> 08:48.166
WHY? WHY WOULD YOU PUT IT
IN THE TOP CUPBOARD?

08:48.291 --> 08:51.041
YOU KNOW I CAN'T REACH THE TOP CUPBOARD.

08:51.166 --> 08:54.458
BOTTOM CUPBOARD. COME ON!
LET'S DO THE BOTTOM CUPBOARD.

09:01.583 --> 09:02.959
WHAT IS THAT?

09:03.041 --> 09:05.667
HUH? CAR GIRL.

09:05.750 --> 09:07.834
IS SHE LIVING HERE?

09:07.917 --> 09:11.875
NOT... LIVING. IT'S MORE LIKE STAYING.

09:11.959 --> 09:13.875
I MEAN, IT<i> IS </i>LIVING HERE

09:13.959 --> 09:18.667
IN THAT SHE'S ALIVE AND... HERE.

09:18.750 --> 09:21.709
BRIAN, I'M GONNA SAVE YOUR LIFE.

09:21.792 --> 09:23.375
AGAIN?

09:23.500 --> 09:24.917
LET'S MAKE A PACT.

09:25.041 --> 09:26.417
A PACT? WHAT ARE WE, 12?

09:26.542 --> 09:29.041
THIS WEEKEND, YOU BREAK UP WITH CAR GIRL.

09:29.125 --> 09:31.583
I'LL BREAK UP WITH MARJORIE.

09:34.542 --> 09:37.041
Y-YOU'RE GONNA BREAK UP WITH MARJORIE?

09:37.166 --> 09:39.667
YEAH. WE'VE BEEN TOGETHER
ALMOST TWO YEARS NOW.

09:39.750 --> 09:41.333
I MEAN, AFTER TWO YEARS

09:41.417 --> 09:43.333
YOU EITHER MOVE IN OR YOU MOVE ON.

09:43.417 --> 09:45.959
AND YOU WANNA MOVE ON. I LIKE MY HOUSE.

09:46.083 --> 09:48.166
I DON'T WANT ALL
HER SWAP MEET CRAP IN THERE.

09:48.250 --> 09:50.166
I MEAN, SHE HAS ALL THESE BOOKS.

09:50.250 --> 09:52.667
SHE'S ALWAYS READING
THESE MEDICAL JOURNALS. SHE'S A DOCTOR.

09:52.750 --> 09:55.083
WELL, SHE'S ALWAYS RIDING ME
'CAUSE I CAN'T REMEMBER

09:55.208 --> 09:56.625
WHETHER SHE LIKES GOOBERS OR JUNIOR MINTS.
JUNIOR MINTS.

09:56.750 --> 10:00.041
WHATEVER. SO YOU WANNA MAKE
THE PACT OR WHAT?

10:04.083 --> 10:06.583
♪♪

10:06.709 --> 10:09.000
KAREN, IT'S OVER.

10:09.083 --> 10:11.000
KAREN, WE GOTTA TALK.

10:11.083 --> 10:12.250
ABOUT WHAT?

10:12.375 --> 10:15.000
ABOUT SLOWING THINGS WAY DOWN.

10:15.083 --> 10:18.291
HOW FAR DOWN? TO STOPPED.

10:18.417 --> 10:20.792
KAREN, I THINK WE SHOULD TALK.

10:20.917 --> 10:22.083
LET'S GO.

10:22.208 --> 10:23.667
WHERE WE GOING?

10:23.750 --> 10:25.458
TO GET THE NEW MATTRESS.

10:25.583 --> 10:28.291
(plastic flapping) WHAT'S THAT SOUND?

10:30.125 --> 10:32.875
SLOW DOWN! IT'S LISTING.
OH, OKAY. DON'T YELL.

10:32.959 --> 10:34.458
I'M NOT YELLING!

10:34.583 --> 10:36.709
GRAB ONTO THE ROPES.

10:38.458 --> 10:40.291
OH, MY GOD. IT<i> IS </i>LISTING.
BRIAN!

10:40.417 --> 10:42.834
(horn honks) OH, MY GOD. HOLD ON!

10:42.959 --> 10:45.625
YOU'RE GOING TOO FAST! IT'S FALLING OFF!

10:45.750 --> 10:47.000
(horn honks) BRIAN!

10:47.125 --> 10:48.792
KAREN... WHAT?!

10:48.875 --> 10:51.542
I WANNA BREAK UP WITH YOU.

10:51.625 --> 10:53.166
(rope snaps)

10:55.500 --> 10:57.959
(sobbing)

10:58.041 --> 11:00.083
YOU NEED SOME HELP?

11:00.166 --> 11:02.792
NO, WE DON'T NEED ANY HELP!

11:02.875 --> 11:05.542
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU ARE?

11:05.625 --> 11:07.834
YOU'RE A SERIAL MONOGAMIST.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.166
YOU GIVE A GIRL HOPE,

11:09.291 --> 11:12.083
AND THEN BOOM! YOU'RE TED BUNDY.

11:12.166 --> 11:13.709
THAT'S SERIAL<i> KILLER.</i>

11:13.834 --> 11:16.000
WHAT ABOUT THE BRUNCH? THE BRUNCH?

11:16.083 --> 11:18.000
YEAH. DAVE AND DEENA'S BRUNCH.

11:18.083 --> 11:20.709
WELL, THOSE ARE ALL<i> MY </i>BEST FRIENDS.

11:20.834 --> 11:23.709
HONEY, PEOPLE ARE GONNA BE HERE
IN 15 MINUTES. AAH!

11:23.834 --> 11:26.417
HEY! SHH! BABY IS SLEEPING! OKAY.

11:26.500 --> 11:28.041
(baby cries)

11:29.291 --> 11:31.375
15 MINUTES. WHAT AM I GONNA WEAR?

11:31.500 --> 11:34.333
WELL, YOU SHOULD WEAR THAT.
YOU LOOK SEXY IN THAT.

11:34.458 --> 11:35.500
I DO?

11:35.583 --> 11:36.792
YEAH. UGH.

11:36.875 --> 11:39.291
HEY.

11:39.375 --> 11:41.875
YOU, UH, REMEMBER WHAT IT USED TO BE LIKE?

11:42.000 --> 11:43.750
YOU KNOW, BEFORE THE KIDS?

11:43.834 --> 11:47.458
NO. (scoffs)

11:47.542 --> 11:51.041
(doorbell rings)

11:51.125 --> 11:53.542
(girl) DADDY, THE PEOPLE ARE HERE!

11:53.667 --> 11:55.375
♪♪

11:55.500 --> 11:57.959
I DON'T WANNA TELL ANYONE YET.
I'M TOO FRAGILE.

11:58.041 --> 11:59.959
I DON'T WANNA SAY ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

12:00.041 --> 12:02.375
OKAY, WE WON'T SAY ANYTHING.

12:02.500 --> 12:05.375
OH, GOSH, YOU GUYS!

12:05.500 --> 12:06.625
HI, GUYS.

12:06.709 --> 12:08.542
HI, BABY.

12:08.625 --> 12:10.333
HEY, DEENA. HI, KAREN.

12:10.417 --> 12:12.625
HOW ARE YOU? BRIAN DUMPED ME.

12:12.709 --> 12:15.709
OH. HE'S TED BUNDY.

12:15.792 --> 12:17.250
OH!

12:19.875 --> 12:21.542
I NEVER REALLY LIKED HER.

12:21.667 --> 12:24.291
YOU HIT IT WITH YOUR HEAD. OKAY?
OKAY.

12:24.375 --> 12:26.041
READY?

12:26.166 --> 12:27.709
ANGELO. HEY, BIG TIME. HEY.

12:27.792 --> 12:28.875
HEY! GOOD. HI.

12:28.959 --> 12:30.750
HEY, BRI.

12:30.875 --> 12:32.500
HEY. HOW'S THAT BABY?

12:32.583 --> 12:37.208
GREAT. I'M HAVING
MY FIRST ULTRASOUND ON MONDAY.

12:37.291 --> 12:38.625
ON MONDAY? I HAVE
A MODELING GIG IN SAN DIEGO.

12:38.750 --> 12:41.208
YOU KNOW WHAT? I'LL CANCEL IT.

12:41.291 --> 12:42.750
I DID IT! GOOD.

12:42.875 --> 12:45.917
MAYBE BRIAN CAN TAKE YOU.
CAN YOU? IT'S AT 10:00.

12:46.041 --> 12:47.875
WHAT, ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

12:47.959 --> 12:51.083
IT'LL BE MY FIRST CHANCE
TO MEET MY NIECE OR NEPHEW. THANKS, MAN.

12:53.750 --> 12:54.917
YO, BRIAN.

12:55.000 --> 12:58.625
(sighs)

12:58.750 --> 13:01.041
I BROKE UP WITH CAR GIRL.

13:01.125 --> 13:03.333
AND ADAM IS BREAKING UP WITH MARJORIE.

13:03.417 --> 13:05.667
REALLY?

13:05.750 --> 13:08.709
WELL, THAT'S A BUMMER, MAN.
I REALLY LIKE MARJORIE.

13:08.792 --> 13:10.375
DAVE!

13:10.458 --> 13:12.792
OH.

13:12.917 --> 13:14.792
<i>OHH.</i>

13:14.917 --> 13:18.750
YEAH. WHAT SHOULD I DO?
THIS IS COMPLICATED.
IT IS COMPLICATED, BRI.

13:18.834 --> 13:20.083
MAYBE I STILL CAN'T DO ANYTHING.

13:20.166 --> 13:22.709
NO, YOU CAN. ADAM'S NOT GONNA CARE.

13:22.792 --> 13:24.792
HE'LL HAVE A NEW GIRL INSIDE OF A WEEK.
YEAH.

13:24.875 --> 13:27.959
AND DON'T YOU THINK
HE'S GONNA BE HAPPY FOR MARJORIE

13:28.083 --> 13:30.333
TO BE WITH YOU INSTEAD OF SOME MUSCLE GUY

13:30.458 --> 13:33.208
WHO'S RICHER AND SMARTER
THAN HE IS? COME ON. THANKS.

13:33.291 --> 13:37.208
ANYTIME, BRO. NEED A LITTLE HELP HERE,
DAVE. YEAH.

13:37.291 --> 13:39.875
LOOK, FAN THE FLAMES.
WATCH THESE. I GOTTA GO.

13:39.959 --> 13:43.750
DID YOU READ MY PROPOSAL?
NO, I DIDN'T, AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M NOT GOING TO.

13:43.834 --> 13:46.750
I'M NOT A SELLOUT.
THEY WANNA BUY THE GAME.
THEY WANNA DISTRIBUTE IT.

13:46.834 --> 13:49.333
THEY DON'T JUST WANT THE GAME.
THEY WANT ZAP MONKEY.

13:49.458 --> 13:51.709
THEY WANT US, OKAY? THEY WANNA
CRACK OPEN OUR SKULLS,

13:51.792 --> 13:54.041
SCOOP OUT THE BRAINS AND TURN US
INTO CORPORATE ZOMBIES.

13:54.166 --> 13:56.000
I'M NOT A ZOMBIE. I'M AN INDEPENDENT,
DEEP IN MY SOUL.

13:56.083 --> 13:57.792
(Deena) DAVE, NOW!

14:05.750 --> 14:07.041
ADAM, HEY, I DID IT.

14:07.166 --> 14:09.041
I BROKE UP WITH CAR GIRL.

14:09.166 --> 14:10.667
OH, HEY, AWESOME, YEAH.

14:10.750 --> 14:12.583
SO, UH, WHAT ABOUT YOU?

14:12.667 --> 14:14.291
I'M AWESOME.

14:14.375 --> 14:16.417
(Deena) HEY!

14:16.500 --> 14:18.667
ADAM. HEY.

14:18.750 --> 14:19.917
YOU'RE LATE. WHERE'S MARJORIE?

14:20.000 --> 14:21.333
UH...

14:21.417 --> 14:22.917
HI, SWEETIE. WHAT HAPPENED?

14:23.000 --> 14:24.500
UM... WHAT HAPPENED?

14:24.625 --> 14:25.500
(chuckles)

14:25.625 --> 14:26.625
THIS.

14:26.709 --> 14:28.667
OH, MY GOD!

14:28.750 --> 14:30.375
YOU GOT ENGAGED?

14:30.500 --> 14:32.458
OH, MY GOD! CONGRATULATIONS.
(Marjorie) THANK YOU.

14:32.542 --> 14:37.375
YOU GUYS, EVERYBODY, UM, UH,
ADAM AND MARJORIE GOT ENGAGED.

14:37.458 --> 14:38.375
AAH!

14:38.458 --> 14:41.542
(laughs)

14:41.667 --> 14:43.417
BRAVO! MWAH!

14:43.542 --> 14:44.917
CONGRATULATIONS.

14:45.041 --> 14:46.417
HEY.

14:46.542 --> 14:49.542
THERE YOU GO, BUDDY. CONGRATULATIONS.

14:49.625 --> 14:53.333
(lowers voice) DID NOT SEE THAT COMING.

14:58.291 --> 15:01.500
OH, AND THEN THERE WAS ONE.

15:07.709 --> 15:09.500
I DON'T UNDERSTAND WHY
YOU'RE DOING THIS, YOU KNOW?

15:09.583 --> 15:12.000
(high-pitched voice) SAY NIGHT-NIGHT.

15:12.083 --> 15:15.125
(both) NIGHT-NIGHT.

15:15.208 --> 15:16.709
(crying) HOW CAN YOU SIT HERE

15:16.834 --> 15:18.417
AND SAY "NIGHT-NIGHT" LIKE THAT?

15:18.500 --> 15:20.375
WELL, I SAID "NIGHT-NIGHT"
AND YOU SAID "NIGHT-NIGHT."

15:20.458 --> 15:22.750
(Deena) WHAT DO YOU THINK THEY'RE SAYING?

15:22.875 --> 15:23.917
"WE COULD STILL BE FRIENDS,"

15:24.000 --> 15:25.917
ALL THAT HORRIBLE BREAKUP STUFF.

15:26.000 --> 15:29.542
"IT'S NOT YOU, CAR GIRL. IT'S ME."

15:29.625 --> 15:31.875
THEY'RE STILL TALKING, HUH?

15:31.959 --> 15:34.500
YEAH.

15:34.583 --> 15:36.667
(shouting)

15:36.750 --> 15:39.750
DO YOU SEE HOW ONE BREAST
IS BIGGER THAN THE OTHER?
YOU'RE KILLING ME!

15:39.875 --> 15:41.250
THE RIGHT ONE.

15:41.375 --> 15:42.417
BINGO.

15:42.500 --> 15:44.959
DON'T CRY. LISTEN, KAREN, KAREN, KAREN.

15:45.083 --> 15:46.625
IT'S THIS WAY.

15:49.917 --> 15:54.500
(gate creaks open, shuts)

16:00.875 --> 16:02.959
COME HERE.

16:03.041 --> 16:06.291
COME ON.

16:06.417 --> 16:09.291
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE PACT?!

16:09.417 --> 16:11.333
DON'T EVER THINK I'D GO BACK ON A PACT,

16:11.458 --> 16:13.875
ESPECIALLY WITH YOU, BRI.
I DIDN'T MAKE THE PACT.

16:13.959 --> 16:16.959
(clenches teeth)
I BROKE UP WITH HER. JEEZ!

16:17.041 --> 16:21.000
LAST NIGHT, I DID IT, AND SHE WAS STELLAR.

16:21.125 --> 16:26.125
I MEAN, SHE WAS LIKE A GUY.
SHE WAS STOIC, CLASSY.

16:26.250 --> 16:29.125
YOU KNOW, THE NEXT MORNING,
I WAKE UP, I'M LOOKING AT HER,

16:29.208 --> 16:31.125
AND SHE LOOKED SO GREAT WEARING

16:31.208 --> 16:34.125
THIS CUTE LITTLE WHITE T-SHIRT
THING SHE WEARS TO BED,

16:34.208 --> 16:36.125
AND I DON'T KNOW. I'M THINKING TO MYSELF,

16:36.208 --> 16:38.792
"WHAT THE HELL AM I DOING?"

16:38.917 --> 16:41.083
I LOVE THIS GIRL.

16:41.166 --> 16:42.875
AND, YOU KNOW, BEFORE I KNOW IT,

16:43.000 --> 16:47.375
WE'RE CRYING AND HAVING, LIKE,
THE BEST SEX OF OUR LIVES,

16:47.500 --> 16:53.375
AND THEN WE WENT OUT AND... BOUGHT A RING.

16:53.500 --> 16:56.083
SHE'S A...

16:56.166 --> 16:58.208
REALLY GREAT GIRL.

16:58.333 --> 17:00.291
YEAH, SEE, THAT'S THE THING.

17:00.375 --> 17:02.208
EVERYONE LOVES HER. EVEN YOU LOVE HER.

17:02.333 --> 17:05.417
I MEAN, WHAT KIND OF IDIOT
WOULD I BE TO LET HER GO?

17:05.500 --> 17:07.542
A BIG IDIOT.

17:07.667 --> 17:10.500
WILL YOU BE MY BEST MAN?

17:12.375 --> 17:13.375
YEAH.

17:13.500 --> 17:15.792
(both chuckling)

17:15.875 --> 17:17.458
DID YOU CALL YOUR MOM?

17:17.542 --> 17:20.333
FORGOT TO CALL MY MOM.

17:21.875 --> 17:23.625
MARRIAGE IS COOL, MAN.

17:23.709 --> 17:26.375
YOU KNOW, YOU GOT THE WHOLE
COMMITMENT THING. THAT'S GREAT.

17:26.500 --> 17:28.208
THE KIDS-- THEY'RE AWESOME, YOU KNOW?

17:28.333 --> 17:30.208
ESPECIALLY IF YOU'RE NOT INTO HAVING SEX.

17:30.333 --> 17:32.375
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, WHEN YOU'RE
MARRIED, YOU DON'T HAVE SEX.

17:32.458 --> 17:34.875
I BET YOU HAVE MORE SEX THAN ME.

17:34.959 --> 17:36.875
WE HAVEN'T HAD SEX FOR-- WELL, LET'S SEE.

17:36.959 --> 17:38.458
CARRIE'S 6 MONTHS OLD,

17:38.542 --> 17:40.417
SO... SIX MONTHS.

17:40.542 --> 17:42.000
(chuckles)

17:42.083 --> 17:44.542
YOU HAVEN'T HAD SEX FOR SIX MONTHS?

17:44.625 --> 17:46.375
LAST TIME WE DID, DEENA WAS PREGNANT.

17:46.500 --> 17:48.875
YOU KNOW, LET'S GET
THE WHOLE LABOR THING GOING.

17:49.000 --> 17:50.875
IT'S NOT EXACTLY EROTIC, MY MAN.

17:51.000 --> 17:52.709
MORE THAN I WANTED TO KNOW.

17:52.834 --> 17:54.375
YEAH. IT'S WEIRD. IT HAPPENS.

18:21.458 --> 18:25.125
DON'T COME DOWN HERE.
JUST DON'T EVEN TRY IT.

18:25.250 --> 18:26.792
WHAT?

18:26.917 --> 18:29.000
I DON'T WANNA TALK TO YOU.

18:29.083 --> 18:31.208
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
DON'T TRY TO "BRIAN" ME EITHER.

18:31.291 --> 18:34.208
I SEE RIGHT THROUGH THAT.
IT MIGHT WORK ON CAR GIRL.

18:34.291 --> 18:36.208
IT'S NOT GONNA WORK ON ME.

18:36.291 --> 18:40.083
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

18:43.000 --> 18:44.917
HE TOLD ME ABOUT THE PACT.

18:45.041 --> 18:46.959
HE SAID THAT YOU TRIED TO GET HIM

18:47.041 --> 18:49.458
TO MAKE A PACT TO BREAK UP WITH ME.

18:49.542 --> 18:51.125
H-HE SAID THAT?

18:54.417 --> 18:56.875
DID YOU THINK THAT
HE<i> SHOULD </i>BREAK UP WITH ME?

18:56.959 --> 18:58.667
I MEAN, WHAT AM I TO YOU? AM I...

18:58.792 --> 19:01.208
AM I LIKE CAR GIRL?
WHAT'S MY NAME--DOCTOR GIRL?

19:01.291 --> 19:03.959
NO. GOD, NO. 'CAUSE I SAW THE LOOK
ON YOUR FACE

19:04.041 --> 19:06.500
WHEN I SHOWED YOU THE RING,
AND YOU WERE SHOCKED.

19:06.625 --> 19:08.375
IT WASN'T SHOCK.

19:08.458 --> 19:09.917
YES, IT WAS.

19:10.000 --> 19:12.291
I KNOW YOU, OKAY?
OR AT LEAST I THOUGHT I DID.

19:12.375 --> 19:13.959
MARJORIE...

19:14.083 --> 19:17.125
YOU KNOW, WHEN I FIRST MET ADAM,
I WASN'T SURE ABOUT HIM.

19:17.250 --> 19:19.125
AND THEN I MET YOU, AND I THOUGHT,

19:19.250 --> 19:23.500
IF THIS GUY IS HIS BEST FRIEND,
HE MUST REALLY HAVE SOMETHING.

19:25.208 --> 19:27.041
COME ON, HONEY. WE GOTTA GO.

19:27.166 --> 19:30.500
I GUESS I WAS WRONG ABOUT ONE OF YOU.

19:30.625 --> 19:34.000
(reggae music playing)

19:36.917 --> 19:38.834
(Adam) SEE YOU LATER, BRI.

19:38.959 --> 19:42.125
♪♪

20:01.083 --> 20:02.625
(dog barks)

20:02.709 --> 20:04.000
KAREN, IT'S ME.

20:04.125 --> 20:06.083
(Karen) WHAT DO YOU WANT?

20:06.166 --> 20:08.083
YOU TOOK MY HOUSE KEY.

20:08.166 --> 20:10.500
I THOUGHT YOU AGREED TO MY CONDITIONS.

20:10.583 --> 20:13.208
WHAT--WHAT CONDITIONS?

20:13.291 --> 20:16.250
KAREN--KAREN, LET ME IN.
THIS IS MY APARTMENT. (dog barks)

20:16.375 --> 20:18.583
KAREN?

20:20.041 --> 20:23.041
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:24.542 --> 20:25.542
(dog barks)

20:27.166 --> 20:29.208
<i>This is Adam Hillman.</i>

20:29.291 --> 20:31.625
<i>I can't get to the phone,</i>

20:31.709 --> 20:33.208
ADAM, IT'S ME.

20:33.333 --> 20:35.250
I'M HEADING UP THERE,
AND I NEED A PLACE TO STAY.

20:35.375 --> 20:37.250
ADAM, PICK UP. I KNOW YOU'RE THERE,

20:37.375 --> 20:40.375
AND I KNOW YOU TOLD MARJORIE
THAT THE PACT WAS MY IDEA

20:40.500 --> 20:42.000
WHEN IT WAS REALLY YOUR IDEA,

20:42.083 --> 20:44.125
AND NOW SHE HATES ME
AND I HAVE TO LET HER.

20:44.208 --> 20:46.875
I'M KNOCKING ON YOUR DOOR IN 20 SECONDS.

20:46.959 --> 20:48.250
(phone picks up)

20:48.375 --> 20:49.875
(Marjorie) Brian, it's Marjorie.

20:50.000 --> 20:51.750
MARJORIE.

20:51.875 --> 20:55.083
Is that true, what you just said?

20:55.208 --> 20:57.917
NO, NO. WHOA, MARJORIE, YOU'RE, UH...

20:58.000 --> 20:59.750
I'M LOSING YOU.

20:59.875 --> 21:02.834
MARJORIE, YOU'RE, UH, BREAKING UP

21:02.917 --> 21:05.625
IN A... BAD POCKET.

21:09.667 --> 21:12.250
ADAM MADE UP THE PACT?

21:18.333 --> 21:21.041
LOOK, I DON'T WANNA TALK
ABOUT IT. HE'S YOUR FRIEND.

21:21.125 --> 21:22.417
HE DID IT TO HELP ME

21:22.542 --> 21:24.250
SO I COULD GET OUT
OF THE THING WITH CAR GIRL.

21:24.375 --> 21:26.250
BRIAN, HE BROKE UP WITH ME.

21:26.375 --> 21:28.417
THAT HAS NOTHING TO DO WITH CAR GIRL.

21:28.542 --> 21:30.417
AND THEN THE NEXT DAY, HE FREAKS OUT,

21:30.542 --> 21:33.458
AND THEN HE PROPOSES TO ME.
HE DOESN'T KNOW WHAT HE WANTS.

21:33.583 --> 21:35.417
HE DOES. JUST CALL HIM. TALK TO HIM.

21:35.500 --> 21:37.417
I CAN'T. HE'S ON A PLANE TO NEW YORK.

21:37.500 --> 21:39.959
AND HE'S PROBABLY HAVING SEX
WITH SOME STEWARDESS

21:40.041 --> 21:42.792
IN THE FIRST CLASS BATHROOM. NO, HE ISN'T.

21:42.917 --> 21:46.959
HE'S THINKING ABOUT DOING THAT,
BUT HE'S NOT DOING IT.

21:47.041 --> 21:48.333
I DON'T KNOW, BRIAN.

21:48.458 --> 21:51.625
I LOVE HIM, BUT HE
DRIVES ME CRAZY, YOU KNOW?

21:55.083 --> 21:57.208
WE'RE GETTING MARRIED.

22:00.083 --> 22:01.959
(sighs)

22:02.083 --> 22:04.709
WHAT DOES IT MATTER HOW WE GOT HERE?

22:04.792 --> 22:06.792
THERE YOU GO.

22:06.875 --> 22:09.041
(sighs)

22:09.125 --> 22:11.041
LISTEN, CALL HIM.

22:12.625 --> 22:16.333
I'M GONNA GO. I'M GONNA STAY
AT MY SISTER'S PLACE.

22:16.417 --> 22:18.417
NO, NO, NO, NO. STAY, STAY, STAY.

22:18.500 --> 22:20.166
PLEASE. UM, I...

22:20.250 --> 22:22.542
PLEASE, PLEASE, IT'S SCARY
UP HERE BY MYSELF.

22:22.667 --> 22:26.500
I CAN'T GO HOME BECAUSE
THEY'RE TENTING FOR TERMITES.

22:26.625 --> 22:27.667
PLEASE.

22:27.792 --> 22:29.333
PLEASE.

22:32.792 --> 22:34.166
YEAH, OKAY.

22:34.250 --> 22:37.166
OKAY, GREAT. SO, UM, WE'LL GET DRUNK.

22:37.250 --> 22:40.417
WE'LL STAY UP TILL 4:00.
IT'LL BE LIKE A SLUMBER PARTY.

22:40.500 --> 22:42.625
AWESOME. YEAH.

22:44.542 --> 22:46.250
HOLD IT.

22:46.333 --> 22:48.166
HOLD IT.

22:48.250 --> 22:52.500
BREATHE THROUGH YOUR SIT BONES.

22:59.208 --> 23:00.542
BEAUTIFUL, DEENA.

23:00.625 --> 23:02.542
YOU'RE REALLY IMPROVING.

23:02.625 --> 23:06.041
ALL RIGHT, EVERYONE.

23:06.125 --> 23:08.375
WARRIOR 2.

23:08.458 --> 23:09.542
AND TURN.

23:09.625 --> 23:15.250
(teakettle whistling)

23:18.583 --> 23:19.875
THEY DOWN?

23:19.959 --> 23:21.333
THEY'RE DOWN.

23:21.417 --> 23:22.709
WANT SOME TEA?

23:22.834 --> 23:25.709
YEAH. OKAY. TEA.

23:35.417 --> 23:37.959
WHY DON'T WE EVER HAVE SEX ANYMORE?

23:38.083 --> 23:40.583
WHAT? WE DON'T HAVE SEX ANYMORE?

23:43.917 --> 23:45.583
I LOVE YOU.

23:45.667 --> 23:47.083
I THINK YOU LOVE ME.

23:47.208 --> 23:49.750
YOU KNOW I LOVE YOU.

23:52.709 --> 23:55.959
BUT SOMETHING'S...
GONE OUT OF IT, YOU KNOW?

23:56.083 --> 23:57.709
YEAH, IT'S THE KIDS.

23:57.792 --> 23:59.667
MAYBE.

23:59.750 --> 24:02.709
MAYBE? THEY SLEEP IN OUR BED
WITH US EVERY NIGHT.

24:08.333 --> 24:10.750
I DON'T FEEL SEXY ANYMORE. AROUND ME.

24:10.834 --> 24:13.458
WELL, DO YOU? AROUND ME?

24:13.583 --> 24:15.583
GOD, I USED TO.

24:18.083 --> 24:20.500
WHAT IF WE, UH, DID SOMETHING?

24:20.625 --> 24:21.917
NOT DOING TANTRIC YOGA.

24:22.000 --> 24:23.959
(chuckles)

24:24.083 --> 24:27.000
WHAT IF WE...

24:27.125 --> 24:29.250
HAD SEX WITH OTHER PEOPLE?

24:29.333 --> 24:31.875
WHAT?

24:31.959 --> 24:33.750
WE GOT MARRIED SO YOUNG, YOU KNOW?

24:33.834 --> 24:37.959
WE MISSED OUT ON THE EXCITEMENT
A LOT OF OTHER PEOPLE HAD.

24:38.041 --> 24:41.667
HONEY, YEAH, SURE. THAT'S, UH, GREAT.

24:46.166 --> 24:50.291
YOU WANT ME TO HAVE INTERCOURSE
WITH ANOTHER WOMAN?

24:50.375 --> 24:52.291
I DON'T WANT YOU TO LEAVE ME OR ANYTHING.

24:52.375 --> 24:55.500
I JUST THOUGHT MAYBE WE COULD
TRY IT, THAT'S ALL.

24:55.625 --> 24:59.208
YOU KNOW, I...

24:59.291 --> 25:01.583
WHA...

25:01.667 --> 25:04.375
AND YOU WOULD SLEEP
WITH SOMEONE ELSE, TOO?

25:04.500 --> 25:07.041
YES.

25:08.542 --> 25:11.250
BUT WOULD WE TELL EACH OTHER
WHAT HAPPENED?

25:11.333 --> 25:12.500
NO, NO.

25:12.625 --> 25:13.625
NO.

25:13.709 --> 25:14.959
NO.

25:16.875 --> 25:19.000
DOESN'T IT KINDA TURN YOU ON?

25:19.125 --> 25:23.792
JUST... TALKING ABOUT IT?

25:23.875 --> 25:25.667
WELL, THAT WOULD BE A YES.

25:25.750 --> 25:28.000
SO...

25:28.083 --> 25:31.792
(moaning)

25:31.875 --> 25:35.000
(mug hits floor) OHH!

25:37.333 --> 25:38.125
MOMMY?

25:38.208 --> 25:40.917
WHOA! HEY, MUFFIN.

25:41.000 --> 25:43.583
WHAT IS DADDY DOING?

25:43.709 --> 25:45.792
OH, NOTHING. MOMMY AND DADDY--
WE WERE JUST...

25:45.875 --> 25:47.542
JUST PLAYING A GAME, HONEY.

25:47.667 --> 25:49.500
I WANT HIM TO STOP.

25:49.583 --> 25:50.875
YEAH, WE'RE STOPPING.

25:51.000 --> 25:53.083
YEAH, WE SHOULD STOP. YEAH.

25:53.208 --> 25:56.667
SORRY, SWEETIE. IT'S OKAY. COME HERE.

26:06.667 --> 26:10.041
(Marjorie) MAYBE WE'LL DO IT IN LAS VEGAS,
(Brian) VEGAS?

26:10.166 --> 26:13.166
BUT YOU NEED TWO WITNESSES.
ME AND CAR GIRL.

26:13.250 --> 26:17.166
I'D RATHER HAVE A STRIPPER THAN CAR GIRL.

26:19.875 --> 26:24.834
SHE CAN'T LOCK YOU
OUT OF YOUR OWN APARTMENT.

26:24.917 --> 26:27.333
WE SHOULD GO OVER THERE, BREAK IN.

26:27.417 --> 26:28.458
WHAT?

26:28.583 --> 26:29.917
WE SHOULD BREAK IN.

26:30.041 --> 26:31.542
WE<i> SHOULD </i>BREAK IN.

26:31.625 --> 26:32.917
IT'S YOUR COMPUTER.

26:33.041 --> 26:34.542
IT<i> IS </i>MY COMPUTER.

26:34.625 --> 26:36.333
SO LET'S DO IT.

26:38.333 --> 26:40.250
YOU MEAN REALLY DO IT?

26:40.333 --> 26:42.375
(laughing) YEAH, I MEAN
REALLY DO IT. COME ON.

26:42.458 --> 26:47.417
SHE DOES TAKE THAT LITTLE RAT
FOR A WALK EVERY NIGHT.

26:47.542 --> 26:50.417
WAIT. STOP.

26:50.500 --> 26:52.250
♪ [ROCK]

26:54.709 --> 26:57.000
COME ON. COME ON.

26:59.667 --> 27:01.417
GO, GO, GO!

27:12.625 --> 27:13.959
LET ME DO IT.

27:14.041 --> 27:16.208
NO, I GOT IT. BRIAN.

27:17.959 --> 27:20.458
(whispering) MARJORIE, HURRY.

27:20.583 --> 27:22.291
OKAY.

27:22.375 --> 27:24.792
IT'S OPEN. IT'S OPEN. GO AROUND FRONT.

27:24.875 --> 27:25.959
OKAY.

27:26.041 --> 27:27.625
♪ [CONTINUES]

27:34.917 --> 27:38.792
GIVE ME THE KEY ON THE HOOK
BY THE DARTBOARD. OKAY.

27:38.917 --> 27:41.041
GOT IT.

27:41.125 --> 27:44.291
BRI, BANANA BREAD. WE SHOULD TAKE IT.

27:44.417 --> 27:45.834
YEAH.

27:45.959 --> 27:48.583
(dog barking outside) GOOD BOY! YES.

27:48.667 --> 27:50.333
(whispering) MARJORIE!

27:50.458 --> 27:53.000
(mouth full) OH, MY GOD. THIS IS
SO GOOD. DID SHE MAKE THIS?

27:53.083 --> 27:55.000
CLOSET! CLOSET!

27:55.083 --> 27:57.250
♪♪

27:57.333 --> 28:00.500
WHY ARE WE HIDING? IT'S YOUR APARTMENT.
BECAUSE SHE'S CRAZY.

28:00.625 --> 28:03.375
(humming)

28:03.500 --> 28:07.667
(Karen) HEY. HEY, YOU LITTLE SCHNOOK.

28:09.917 --> 28:15.000
(growling and barking)

28:23.250 --> 28:27.834
WHAT ARE YOU DOING? COME HERE.

28:27.959 --> 28:30.875
MAN. BRIAN IS SUCH A PIG.

28:31.000 --> 28:32.375
(muffled laughter)

28:32.458 --> 28:34.208
(Karen) COME ON. LET'S GO TO BED.

28:34.291 --> 28:38.375
(baby voice) LET'S GO TO BED,
MY LITTLE NEEDLE. YES.

28:38.500 --> 28:40.375
REALLY LONG DAY.

29:00.291 --> 29:02.208
